OL,3,CRobert Jenrick: Scrap the Sentencing
OL,4,CCouncil to prevent 'two-tier' justice
OL,6,FRobert Jenrick will vow to abolish the
OL,7,FSentencing Council when he addresses
OL,8,Fthe Conservative Party conference on
OL,9,FTuesday.
OL,11,FThe shadow justice secretary is
OL,12,Fexpected to set out plans to put
OL,13,Fministers in charge of sentencing
OL,14,Fpolicy, arguing that the current
OL,15,Fsituation has resulted in a "two-tier
OL,16,Fnightmare" with people treated
OL,17,Fdifferently by the courts.
OL,19,FHe will say: "The Sentencing Council
OL,20,Fis not fit for purpose.
